Program: Last Word
Title: David Bowie, Alan Rickman, Olwyn Hughes and Ed Stewart
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b06vn923
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 17 Jan 2016
Matthew Bannister on David Bowie, art expert, fashion icon and media manipulator. Alan Rickman, the actor most famous for playing villains from the Sheriff of Nottingham to Professor Snape. Olwyn Hughes, the sister of the poet Ted Hughes who fiercely guarded his literary legacy and that of his late wife Sylvia Plath. And Ed "Stewpot" Stewart, the Radio 1 and 2 DJ who presented Junior Choice. Show less